## Fix 8: `emitLoadCR7` — Loads CPSR Bits 31..28 into CR7

ARM condition flags are in CPSR bits 31..28 (N,Z,C,V). PPC `mtcrf` with mask 0x01 loads GPR bits 31..28 into CR7 bits 31..28. This mapping needs to be consistent:

```cpp
// Verify: CPSR = N[31] Z[30] C[29] V[28] ...
// CR7 field = bits 31..28 of GPR when loaded with mtcrf 0x01, rs
// CR7[0]=LT, CR7[1]=GT, CR7[2]=EQ, CR7[3]=SO
// When mtcrf 0x01, rs: CR7 bits = rs bits 31..28
// So: CR7[LT=bit31]=N, CR7[GT=bit30]=Z, CR7[EQ=bit29]=C, CR7[SO=bit28]=V

// condPpc mappings (CRn bit numbering: CR7 starts at bit 28 of CR register)
// CR7_LT = CRbit 28 (N)
// CR7_GT = CRbit 29 (Z)  
// CR7_EQ = CRbit 30 (C)
// CR7_SO = CRbit 31 (V)
// In PPC bc instruction, BI field for CR7: LT=28, GT=29, EQ=30, SO=31

static CB condPpc(uint8_t c) {
    // BO=12 means "branch if CRbi SET", BO=4 means "branch if CRbi CLEAR"
    switch (c) {
        case 0:  return {12, 29, true};  // EQ: Z set  (CR7_GT = CPSR_Z)
        case 1:  return { 4, 29, true};  // NE: Z clear
        case 2:  return {12, 30, true};  // CS/HS: C set  (CR7_EQ = CPSR_C)
        case 3:  return { 4, 30, true};  // CC/LO: C clear
        case 4:  return {12, 28, true};  // MI: N set  (CR7_LT = CPSR_N)
        case 5:  return { 4, 28, true};  // PL: N clear
        case 6:  return {12, 31, true};  // VS: V set  (CR7_SO = CPSR_V)
        case 7:  return { 4, 31, true};  // VC: V clear
        // GE/LT/GT/LE/HI/LS need multi-bit checks — fall back to interpreter
        case 8:  return { 0,  0, false}; // HI: C&&!Z — complex
        case 9:  return { 0,  0, false}; // LS: !C||Z — complex
        case 10: return { 0,  0, false}; // GE: N==V — complex
        case 11: return { 0,  0, false}; // LT: N!=V — complex
        case 12: return { 0,  0, false}; // GT: !Z&&N==V — complex
        case 13: return { 0,  0, false}; // LE: Z||N!=V — complex
        case 14: return {20,  0, true};  // AL: always
        default: return { 0,  0, false};
    }
}
```

