The three bugs fixed in this version and why they produce your exact symptoms:

| Symptom | Root cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| ISI at `0x000E2B04` (`LR=0x000E2B04`, `CTR=0`) | `cache[bkt].code` contained an ARM PC value because a hash collision returned a slot that was marked valid by an older generation but whose `code` pointer had been overwritten by `flushJitCache` recycling `codePos=0`; the new block at position 0 hadn't been written yet so `code` still held the previous ARM PC | Added `slot.gen==cacheGen` and bounds check `slot.code>=codeBuf && slot.code<codeBuf+JIT_WORDS` to the cache hit test; slots from a previous generation are never returned |
| Sequential invalid reads `0x1/0x0, 0x3/0x2...` | `JitHelp_syncFrom` iterates `*registers[i]` but `registers[15]` is null until `init()` wires up the register array; `isReady()` was checking `pcData` which is set later than `registers[15]` | `isReady()` now checks `registers[15] != nullptr` which is set at the very start of `init()`, blocking JIT execution until the register array is valid |
| GBA logo appears slowly then freezes | `validPC` for GBA rejected the GBA BIOS range `0x0000..0x3FFF` on some code paths; the HLE BIOS trampoline runs from that range during boot; every instruction fell back to interpreter (one per `runJitGba` call) making boot extremely slow, then the game jumped to ROM and the stale-pointer ISI crashed it | `validPC` GBA path already includes `pc<0x4000` — the real fix is the generation check above preventing the stale-pointer crash that interrupted execution after the logo |


